The code that's hanging up here is in add.go at this [line](https://github.com/containers/buildah/blob/master/add.go#L358).  It's triggered because the `filepath.Rel(contextDir, glob)` call a few lines up is failing as it designed.  The value for contextDir is `/` and the glob is `root/test.txt`.  As the Rel() function just looks at those two strings that are given it, the glob is not relative to the contextDir in this instance. 

If you pass in `/root/test.txt` instead to the add command, then it works.  Similar comment for @amakeenk , but in a different section of add.go.

@nalind @rhatdan, I can change the code to work around this by joining the contextdir and the file and retrying rel again like this:  

```
# git diff
diff --git a/add.go b/add.go
index 1c1f116d..01a06899 100644
--- a/add.go
+++ b/add.go
@@ -355,7 +355,11 @@ func (b *Builder) Add(destination string, extract bool, options AddAndCopyOption
                for _, glob := range localSourceStat.Globbed {
                        rel, err := filepath.Rel(contextDir, glob)
                        if err != nil {
-                               return errors.Wrapf(err, "error computing path of %q", glob)
+                               localFile := filepath.Join(contextDir, glob)
+                               rel, err = filepath.Rel(contextDir, localFile)
+                               if err != nil {
+                                       return errors.Wrapf(err, "error computing path of %q", localFile)
+                               }
                        }
                        if strings.HasPrefix(rel, ".."+string(os.PathSeparator)) {
                                return errors.Errorf("possible escaping context directory error: %q is outside of %q", glob, contextDir)
```
But I'm not sure if that's the approach to take or not.  Thoughts?
